HEADWORD: Spirochaete
<hw>Spi`ro*chae"te</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>spira</ets> a coil + Gr. <?/<?/<?/ hair.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>A genus of Spirobacteria similar to Spirillum, but distinguished by
its motility. One species, the <spn>Spirochaete Obermeyeri</spn>, is
supposed to be the cause of relapsing fever.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

